caption.text: This quirky lemon juicer is designed to encourage the user to juice manually. Inspired by the wringing action of extracting liquids from clothes, WRINGER achieved its seamless minimalistic but intriguing geometry. The folds covering its surface creates ergonomic support for the had to rest and juice comfortably. WRINGER requires two hands on its usage and the thread mechanism helps to minimize the muscle power needed to squeeze a lemon. The product stand on its base and not the other as a way to explain that the juice goes on one side instead of the other. #industrialdesign #rmit #immersiveb√ºro #studio #studentwork
